EVRAZ North America Building New Heat Treat Facility in Alberta | Business Wire
























































EVRAZ North America Building New Heat Treat Facility in Alberta






May 11, 2017 10:57 AM Eastern Daylight Time



CHICAGO--(BUSINESS WIRE)--EVRAZ North America announced it has approved engineering design work 
      and ordering of long-lead time equipment to install a new heat treatment 
      line at its Red Deer, Alberta, Oil Country Tubular Goods facility.
    


      "This project will allow us to better meet the growing need for premium 
      OCTG products by approximately doubling the installed OCTG heat treat 
      capacity in this region" said Conrad Winkler, President and CEO of EVRAZ 
      North America. "This project, along with prior projects that expanded 
      premium threading capacity and increased our premium connections 
      offering, demonstrates our commitment to supporting the evolving 
      requirements of energy exploration companies in North America."
    

About EVRAZ


      EVRAZ North America plc (the Company) is a wholly owned subsidiary of 
      EVRAZ plc, one of the largest vertically integrated steel and mining 
      businesses in the world. The Company is a leading North American 
      producer of engineered steel products for rail, energy and industrial 
      end markets. The Company has six production sites located in the USA 
      (Portland, Oregon; Pueblo, Colorado) and Canada (Regina, Saskatchewan; 
      Calgary, Camrose and Red Deer, Alberta).
    

      EVRAZ is a registered trademark of EVRAZ Group S.A.
    


Contacts

      EVRAZ North America plcChristian MessmacherVP Strategy312-533-3520mediainquiries@evrazna.com

















Contacts

      EVRAZ North America plcChristian MessmacherVP Strategy312-533-3520mediainquiries@evrazna.com







 
 

 






