About EVRAZ




About EVRAZ
EVRAZ North America is a leading North American steel manufacturer producing more than five million tons annually of flat, long, and tubular steel products for major markets including infrastructure, defense, energy and rail.  Its six operations are located in Portland, Ore.; Regina, Saskatchewan; Pueblo, Colo.; Calgary, Camrose and Red Deer, Alberta. 

EVRAZ is the number one producer of large diameter pipe, a leading producer of steel plate and the largest producer of rail in North America. The company is also the largest producer of oil country tubular goods and the largest recycler in western Canada.  EVRAZ North America is a wholly owned subsidiary of EVRAZ plc, one of the largest vertically integrated steel and mining businesses in the world.
The EVRAZ advantage goes beyond our product offerings to the location of our manufacturing facilities in close proximity to transportation and energy hubs.  Our Research and Development complex in Regina and Product Technology Centers in Pueblo and Portland enhance our ability to develop high strength steel products for the most demanding applications.
EVRAZ North America has the facilities and equipment capabilities to meet our customers' needs, backed by outstanding team members who are committed to continuously improving quality, customer service, efficiency and safety.









News



July 30, 2014
 	 EVRAZ North America Announces New Semi-Premium Connection, EVRlock  Connections Brand and Microsite

                        CHICAGO (July 30, 2014) – EVRAZ North America is pleased to introduce a semipremium connection and announce its new EVRlock connections brand. The company has manufactured its successful QB2 premium connection since the late 1990's, and has now expanded its product line with the EVRlock QB1-HT semi-premium connection. 
                    



